                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/539.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Bailey</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Bailey reports the arrival of Zelaya and says about 300 Central Americans and
                    Mexican private citizens tendered him an enthusiastic reception at the
                    train.</p>
                <p rend="center">(To be continued in <ref target="frus1910">Foreign Relations,
                        1910</ref>.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
